: "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2024-01-25T08:26:06.35-06:00", "bill_text": "An Act to limit reliance upon secondary sources as statements of law. Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of South Dakota: Section 1. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 2-14: A secondary source, including any legal treatise, scholarly publication, textbook, or other explanatory text, does not constitute the law or public policy of this state and is not authoritative if the secondary source purports to create, eliminate, expand, or restrict a cause of action, right, or remedy, or if it conflicts with, or is not otherwise addressed by: (1) The Constitution of the United States or of this state; (2) A statute of this state; (3) Case law precedent of this state; or (4) Other common law that may have been adopted by this state."}, {"bill_id": 25166, "bill_version_id": 265293, "bill_version": "House Judiciary Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2024-02-12T14:18:43.053-06:00", "bill_text": "An Act to limit reliance upon secondary sources as statements of law. Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of South Dakota: Section 1. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 2-14: In an action brought in a court in the state, the court may not apply a principle from the American Law Institute's Restatement of the Law, Liability Insurance, in ruling on an issue in the case unless the principle is clearly expressed in a statute of the state, the common law, or case law precedent of the state."}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 25166, "action_date": "2024-01-25T13:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 262421, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/262421.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 175, "committee_id_action": 1197, "committee_id_assigned": 1198, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 25166, "action_date": "2024-02-12T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 265037, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdle